cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and its application to Second Language Acquisition. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as Answer Set Programming is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to predict how learners of English would interpret sentences. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the formalization of a theory in ASP, which involves computational complexity considerations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper presents a system, PIas, that uses the predictions to assist language instructors in designing teaching materials, which involves software engineering considerations.
